About 500 students in various tertiary institutions  have been given scholarships by the Bida local government area of Niger State. To mark his 100 days in the office at the weekend, the council chairman, Hon. Suleiman Sheshi, said that the gesture was to promote education in the area and reduce the number of out-of-school children. Sheshi said that those who benefited were students studying in universities, polytechnics and colleges of education as well as other institutions like nursing and colleges of health technology. He said that within three months in the office his administration has also purchased JAMB forms for 500 students and 400 for NAPTIP while over 300 women petty  traders were given  cash to support their businesses. The chairman, who said that two classrooms were also renovated at Tadafu wards, added that boreholes had been rehabilitated in seven wards. “We have rehabilitate township roads by filling the potholes across the local government area and also construction of roundabout is ongoing, we also purchased ambulance vehicle,” he added. The chairman commended Niger State governor, Alhaji Abubakar Sani Belllo and the council members for supporting his administration. He also thanked the Etsu Nupe, who is also the chairman of the Niger State Traditional Rulers’ Council, Alhaji Yahaya Abubakar, All Progressives Congress (APC) members and others for their support.